.TH "nfp_net_get_mac_addr" 9 "nfp_net_get_mac_addr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nfp_net_get_mac_addr \- Get the MAC address.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" nfp_net_get_mac_addr
.BI "(struct nfp_pf *pf "  ","
.BI "struct net_device *netdev "  ","
.BI "struct nfp_port *port "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pf" 12
NFP PF handle
.IP "netdev" 12
net_device to set MAC address on
.IP "port" 12
NFP port structure
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
First try to get the MAC address from NSP ETH table. If that
fails generate a random address.
